name: Authentic Ripple Pipe! 1 3/4-inch Bolt-On or Weld-On
description:
Ok, the original stuff is rare and thin! Ours has been perfected and doled out in SMALL quantities for about 7 years now. While there are alternatives these days (don't even be fooled for that 2 1/4" Pep Boys crap!), this is the most authentic and proportioned ripple pipe out there and MADE IN THE USA! 
Available in short and long pieces in weld-on and bolt-on applications all in 1 3/4-inch diameter.

BOLT-ON pieces have a nice finished belled tip and feature built in clamping, so no ugly clamps needed. Short are about 13" overall length and long are about 17". These come SHOW CHROMED with hardware!
 
WELD-ON pieces come are mild steel and are fully polished ready for chrome plating once you weld them on your pipes. Short pieces are 11" and have a belled tip, long pieces are 17" and have a straight tip. 

PRICE IS PER EACH PIECE

name: FMA SHORT VELOCITY STACKS
description:
We made a deal with our Friend T-Bone of NOISE when we decided to sell his parts biz and wound up with the rights to the skinny cycle parts he was making. So here is the FMA Short Stack Velocity stack for several different carburator bolt patterns. We make them for the ever popular S&S Super-E/G carbs and we also have them for older S&S Super B/L-Series/Bendix carbs! That's right! They are only a mere 1 1/8-inch deep and 3-inches in diameter. 

*NOW AVAILABLE FOR LINKERTS!
*NOW AVAILABLE FOR CV carbs!

Each stack comes with hardware and a screen and are only available in a polished finish for the time being. Chome will be available soon.

name: FMA Enrichener Knob for SUPER-E
description:
This handy-dandy enrichener/choke knob for the S&S SUPER-E carb. this knob is a must for anyone NOT running a stock S&S air cleaner and is a perfect match with our velocity stacks. 

David Beckham has one on his Garage Company-built knucklehead!

name: Knucklehead Cork Rocker Tin Gasket Set
description:
A first in the world of knucklehead gaskets is our FMA 1/16 high quality cork rocker tin gasket sets. 70 year-old rocker tins have seen better days and since there are only paper gaskets available until now, they have always been prone to leaking. 
Pop your rocker tins off, clean both surfaces, Gaska-Cinche them, install, be done with leaks!

name: Asphalt Gods-Pictorial History of the Heathens MC
description:
Our good friend Gabe Griffin has been working on this book, which is a historical pictorial of the Heathens MC, for years now which is out and we are proudly selling them. He has been working on a documentary for a few years too...stay tuned.
Don't miss this limited piece of copper History!

From Gabe about the project:
This is a project that has been on the top of my OCD list for the last three or four years. I started out playing music with lyrics from a 60's club members point of view and that turned into a three camera, two car shoot from California to South Dakota to interview the original members of the Venice and South Bay Heathens Motorcycle Family. Crazy. I couldn't believe I was going to actually do it while I was coordinating the camera crew and renting vehicles. If someone came to me and said "hey, I'm going to hang out with this motorcycle gang that I met. You want to bring a video camera and film it?" I would think that guy was crazy. Motorcycle clubs don't put up with that shit. Well, this group liked me enough to let me sit down with them and tell the story of the rise and fall of their club in the 70's and 80's. Hours and hours and hours of video footage, interviews, hundreds of vintage photos collected and too many crazy stories to tell in one sitting. That turned into the book that you see here. It turns out editing is extremely expensive and this movie is going to take a good chunk of time in the editing booth.

name: N.O.S. Frisco Choppers Tee circa 1980s
description:
THESE ARE NOT REPRODUCTIONS!! We are NOT printing these they are New but Old Stock from almost 30 years ago. The skull motor logo is on the front and the "in the ghetto" 3rd street bridge logo on the back. 


We bought out the inventory of 300 mostly N.O.S. old chopper and HD shirts from the '70s through about '87. The shop was in the San Fernando Valley and we are selling these with permission from the family of the passed on that owned it all. Check back often, we have lots of shirts to put up.
